<definition xml:id="lecture-notes-def-e">
    <statement>
        <p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The mathematical constant <m>e</m> is an irrational number approximately equal to <m>2.71828</m>.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        The function <m>\exp(x) = e^x</m> is called the <term>natural exponential function</term>.
